<a name="Related Systems">
<h3>
1.5.  Related Systems
</h3>
</a>
<p>
Widely used commercial systems that provide functionality comparable to the
Test Tool include
<ul>
<a href="http://www.classmarker.com/">
<li>
Class Marker
</a>
<li>
<a href="http://www.quizegg.com">
QuizEgg
</a>
<li>
<a href="https://www.goconqr.com/en-US">
GoConqr
</a>
<li>
<a href="http://web.uvic.ca/hrd/hotpot/">
Hot Potatoes
</a>
<li>
<a href="https://www.quizmeonline.net">
Quiz Me Online
</a>
<li>
<a href="https://www.quizrevolution.com/">
Quiz Revolution
</a>
</ul>
<p>
Each of these systems provides a wide variety of test generating
functionality.  In terms of such functionality, the goal for the Test Tool
is to provide the important core features found in these tools, not the full
range of features found in all of them.  The Test Tool provides functional improvements 
in one area, when compared to most commercially available tools.  These improvements are:
<ul type=a>
<p> <li>
Better Question Customization
<ul>
<li> more question types
<li> different point values assignment to questions
<li> difficulty ranking assignment to questions
<li> subject/topic assignment to questions 

</ul>

</ul>
<p>
The goal for the Test Tool relating to random test generation with questions 
from a question bank is not met by any of the above commercial systems.
